RSSBOT
======

Welcome to RSSBOT, display rss feeds in your irc channel ! see https://pypi.org/project/botlib/

I N S T A L L
=============

you can download with pip3 and install globally:

::

 > sudo pip3 install rssbot

You can also download the tarball and install from that, see https://pypi.org/project/rssbot/#files

if you want to run the bot 24/7 you can install RSSBOT as a service for
the systemd daemon. You can do this by copying the following into
the /etc/systemd/system/rssbot.service file:

::

 [Unit]
 Description=RSSBOT - display rss feeds in your irc channel
 After=network-online.target
 Wants=network-online.target
 
 [Service]
 ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/rssbot mods=irc,rss
 
 [Install]
 WantedBy=multi-user.target

then add the rssbot service with:

::

 > systemctl enable rssbot
 > systemctl daemon-reload

to configure the bot use the cfg (config) command, use sudo for the system daemon
and without sudo if you want to run the bot locally:

::

 > sudo rssbotbot cfg server=irc.freenode.net channel=\#dunkbots nick=botje
 > sudo service botd stop
 > sudo service botd start

if you don't want the bot to startup at boot, remove the service file:

::

 > sudo rm /etc/systemd/system/rssbot.service


U S A G E
=========

to add an url use the rss command with an url:

> rssbot rss https://news.ycombinator.com/rss
ok 1

run the rss command to see what urls are registered:

> rssbot rss
0 https://news.ycombinator.com/rss

the fetch command can be used to poll the added feeds:

> rssbot fetch
fetched 0


